HEADWORD: Drunkard
<hw>Drunk"ard</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Drunk</ets> +
<ets>-ard</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who habitually drinks strong liquors
immoderately; one whose habit it is to get drunk; a toper; a
sot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>drunkard</qex> and glutton shall come to poverty.</q>
<rj><qau> Prov. xxiii. 21.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drunken</ent>⟦br⟧
